snippet.textDisplay:
Wow... 10 things you didnt need to know and nothing of relevance needed to know.


What is the stance on physical media and offline capability is the primary one.


Also


Clearly the design is intended for vertical usage. That also stems from the primary vent and the whole console being laid out in a smokestack format. Yet the problem that creates is CONSOLES CANT HANDLE READING DISCS FOR SHIT VERTICALLY!!!!!!!! Seriously, this configuration destroys disc drives and has for the last 2 generations since they started pushing it. So how is that going to play out? You lay the thing down to protect the disc drive and you will have overheating as the thing is not optimized to vent heat through that top (unless they change the design) OR you have to run the risk of the disc drive failing within a year.


This seriously smacks of Microsoft being Microsoft and in their "infinite wisdom" trying to Mojave the public yet again and tell us what we need rather than producing what we want. If you can see glaring issues within the first bit of info its a guarantee that this ideology WILL pervade the whole system and its design choices.

snippet.textDisplay:
The GPU in both the PS4 and XBOX One wasn't really the issue. It was the CPU, so it makes sense the GPU is only double the power, while the CPU is 4x what we currently have. That'll help for world generation, texture streaming, and keeping a stable framerate on any kind of game really.

But the proof is in the pudding, as they say, and I will wait until proper reviews are out. If it isn't at least 1080p and 60 FPS constantly, then I'll wait, or just build a desktop PC that will wipe the floor with both the PS5 and XBOX whatever the hell it's called come launch.

I have an NVME M.2 SSD in my laptop as a boot drive, and I would never go back. Windows 10 boots up - with fast start up turned off - in about 15 seconds. If the XBOX has one of those in it, that's a game changer for sure. Those things rock. Would love to get another NVME drive at 1 TB to replace the 5400 drive in my laptop but I'm not so impatient to need my games to load up right now.
